  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Invoicing gives your company tools to manage customers and corporate clients with net terms. Invoicing is available to users on our Advanced and Professional plans.</p><p>In order to invoice a ticket, it must have either a customer with billing terms enabled or a billing agent attached to the ticket. The ticket must be progressed to Waiting for Payment status before it can be invoiced. After creating an invoice, there may be times when you need to refund a payment or void the invoice altogether. The tutorials below will guide you through different scenarios.\u00a0</p><h3 id=\"Invoicing:RefundingandVoidingInvoices-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196827/Invoicing+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196827\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196840/Invoicing+Creating+and+Managing+Invoices\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196840\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing: Creating and Managing Invoices</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934229611/Invoicing+Editing+Tickets+on+Invoices\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934229611\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoices: Editing Tickets on Invoices</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934327961/Invoicing+Remittance+and+Reconciling+Invoices\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934327961\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Invoicing: Remittance and Reconciling Invoices</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Invoicing:RefundingandVoidingInvoices-RefundingaChargeonanInvoice\">Refunding a Charge on an Invoice</h2><p>Users can perform a refund on partially paid invoices as well as invoices that are paid in full. When viewing an invoice, the Payments section lists any payments/refunds applied to the invoice. To begin a refund, click the Refund button next to the appropriate ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Invoicing:RefundingandVoidingInvoices-IfPaymentWasTakenandtheTicketisstillOpen\">If Payment Was Taken and the Ticket is still Open</h3><p>A partially paid ticket will show as Unpaid on the invoice view. Begin the refund by clicking the <strong>Refund</strong> <strong>button</strong> next to the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You will be prompted to confirm the refund amount and how you would like to refund the customer.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"448\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%203.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Cancel Save</strong> - Cancel the refund transaction</p></li><li><p><strong>Credit Customer</strong> - Issue a credit balance to the customer/agent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Issue Cash/Check</strong> - Issue a cash/check refund to the customer.</p></li></ul><p>After finalizing the refund, the transaction will be reflected in the payment history of the invoice. The details will include the original payment ID for the transaction that was originally taken. If you need to remove the ticket from the invoice, you can do so from the Remittance page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%204.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"Invoicing:RefundingandVoidingInvoices-IfPaymentWasTakenandtheTicketisClosed\">If Payment Was Taken and the Ticket is Closed</h3><p>If full payment has been taken for a ticket on the invoice, it is automatically moved to Closed status after saving remittance. If you are performing a refund with a return, there are additional steps necessary to resolve the ticket.</p><p /><p>A fully paid ticket will show as Paid on the invoice view. Begin the refund by clicking the <strong>Refund button</strong> next to the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>You will be prompted to confirm the refund amount and how you would like to refund the customer.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"448\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%206.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Cancel Save</strong> - Cancel the refund transaction</p></li><li><p><strong>Credit Customer</strong> - Issue a credit balance to the customer/agent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Issue Cash/Check</strong> - Issue a cash/check refund to the customer.</p></li></ul><p /><p>After finalizing the refund, the transaction will be reflected in the payment history of the invoice. The details will include the original payment ID for the transaction that was originally taken. Even though the payment has been reversed, the ticket is still in Closed status. Under the Invoice Items section of the page, click the <strong>Ticket Link</strong> to view the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%208.5.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When viewing the ticket, you can see that the ticket is in Closed status with a balance due. The transaction and refund have been posted, but the item(s) will need to be returned. Click the <strong>Start a Return button</strong> along the row of ticket options.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%208.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Follow the standard return process. Select the item(s) to return and move them into the appropriate inventory status. Add notes and click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>After you have returned all items and the ticket has a zero balance, save the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"224\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Invoicing:RefundingandVoidingInvoices-VoidinganInvoice\">Voiding an Invoice</h2><p>Users can void an invoice by removing all linked tickets. You can do this on the Remittance page for the invoice.</p><p /><p>Under the Invoice Items section of the Remittance page, click the <strong>Remove button</strong> to unlink tickets from the invoice. Once all linked tickets have been removed, click<strong> Save Remittance</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%2013.5.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The invoice will show Voided status, and the tickets can be edited to return items back to inventory and closed.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934917724/Invoice%20Refund%2013.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
